          "email": "uja.ornl@gmail.com",
          "date": "2014-08-22 15:54:37.000000000",
          "tz": -240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2827 ldlm: wrong handling of ldlm resends (ORNL version)",
        "message": "LU-2827 ldlm: wrong handling of ldlm resends (ORNL version)\n\nIf a successful reply is lost for an intent\nlock request, MDS will not correctly recover\nfrom this situation on resend. Instead, a new\nlock is created.\n\nThis patch also adds handling of resend during layout-lock.\n\nThis patch is the merge + b2_4 back-port of the following\n2 patches to the special ORNL 2.4 server tree. This is done\nto see what regression are in the LU-2827 patch that has\nbeen modified so it can be applied to the ORNL lustre code\nbase :\n\nLustre-commit: I9a23c13313d5168d0c232fdc0acbdab330089356\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/5978/\n\nLustre-commit: Ideb551779a884d77ded8036c513f62557b2dfcde\nLustre-change: http://review.whamcloud.com/10378\n\nSigned-off-by: Vitaly Fertman <vitaly_fertman@xyratex.com>\nSigned-off-by: Bruno Faccini <bruno.faccini@intel.com>\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@gmail.com>\nChange-Id: Idbe40b4b2fb819a5418d55c98f2f3814c955c5b5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_4"
    }
